Title: Where to Buy Sheet Music Online?
Description: There are good options for buying music online for children's musical instruments . Which online retailer should you use depends on the price and delivery costs . It also depends on whether you want a physical copy of the music you are looking for .  Amazon have copies of “Hedwig’s Theme” from Harry Potter available . This is an affiliate link, so I may earn a small commission if you make a purchase after following this link .  ABRSM sell copies of the music set for their exam syllabus online on their own website . Trinity College London offer graded exams for a number of musical instruments . Sheet Music Direct have a large catalogue of music to choose for most instruments .  The next post will look at large retailers such as Waterstones . I will do a post talking about where you can go to a physical shop to purchase sheet music . I am always looking for ideas for the blog .

Title: Miles Davis (1926-1991): The Greatest Jazz Artist? , Sheet Music Library (PDF)
Description: Miles Davis has been voted the greatest jazz artist of all time in 2015 . The trumpeter beat the likes of Louis Armstrong, Ella Fitzgerald and Billie Holiday – all of whom made the top 10 .  Miles Davis’ Kind of Blue is the “best-selling jazz record of all time” (Rolling Stone) The success of the record can rightfully be attributed to Davis' productive creativity . Davis had a knack for recognizing talent, and he “launched the careers” of many notable jazz musicians . His 1970 record, Bitches Brew is considered the foundation of jazz-rock fusion .  Bitches Brew (Rolf and Watts) was certified platinum (1 million copies sold) by the Recording Industry Association of America in 2003 (RIAA) Many credit the album with a resurgence in jazz popularity and commercial sales throughout the ‘70s . The album became known as “cool jazz”; indicative of where its popularity took hold .  Louis Armstrong’s music in the 1920s, in particular on his Hot Five and Hot Seven recordings from 1925-1929, is considered by some to be “the most exciting and influential in jazz music” (Rolf and Watts 46) While Armstrong continued to play jazz trumpet with masterful skill after the ‘20s, he turned his productive efforts to being a singer and entertainer .  Miles Davis, Louis Armstrong, Charlie Parker, Duke Ellington, and others are deserving of admiration, respect, and recognition for their significant contribution to jazz . But only one can claim the designation, “most influential,” and that belongs solely to Davis .  Davis, Francis.  Kind Of Blue [Legacy Edition].  Legacy/Columbia/Legacy, 2009 CD. “Miles Followed His Heart’s ‘followed his heart’. ‘The Children of ‘Bitches Brew’ ” Rolling Stone 28 Dec.  1978: Web. 12 Mar. 2016 . Title: FREDERIC MOMPOU (CATALAN COMPOSER AND PIANIST) With Sheet Music To Download , Sheet Music Library (PDF)
Description: Mompou was a Catalan composer of lyric songs and piano miniatures . His music is characterized by Impressionist elegance, simple and direct melody, and the haunting, deep emotions of folk music .  The music of the Catalan composer Frederic Mompou (1893–1987) is radically simple, spare, mystical, and utterly unclassifiable as to style . The work he regarded as a summation of his life’s efforts was given the quizzical title Música callada—(music that has fallen silent) Find his complete sheet music in our Library .  Mompou studied music at the Paris Conservatory in 1911 . His first published work was a set of piano pieces called Impresiones intimas (Intimate Impressions), written between 1911 and 1914 . Like Claude Debussy, he eschewed strong sense of directional motion in music .  Mompou's lifetime output was slender, amounting to about 200 mostly short pieces collected into a few dozen sets . Like Maurice Ravel, he was fascinated by the world of childhood and the musical creativity that seemed to reside near its surface .  Federico Mompou composed 28 pieces in Música callada (four albums, 1959–67), never move faster than a moderate tempo; in free rhythms, they are unassuming yet strangely powerful . He branched out beyond piano music after World War II, writing a number of Catalonian-language songs . Title: Keith Jarret, Jan Garbarek & "Belonging Quartet" , Sheet Music Library (PDF)
Description: Keith Jarrett (born May 8, 1945) is an American jazz and classical music pianist and composer . Jarrett started his career with Art Blakey, moving on to play with Charles Lloyd and Miles Davis . His album The Köln Concert (1975) became the best-selling piano recording in history .  The Charles Lloyd Quartet's 1966 album Forest Flower was one of the most successful jazz recordings of the mid-1960s . The Quartet’s tours across America, Europe, and Moscow made Jarrett a popular musician in rock and jazz . Jarrett joined the Miles Davis group after the trumpeter heard him in a New York City club .  Jarrett recorded a few solo pieces live under the guidance of Miles Davis at Washington’s music club The Cellar Door in December 1970 . In the mid/late 1970s, Jarrett led a “European quartet” with saxophonist Jan Garbarek, bassist Palle Danielsson and drummer Jon Christensen .  In 1973, Jarrett began playing totally improvised solo concerts . The Köln Concert became the best-selling piano recording in history . In the late 1990s, Jarrett was diagnosed with chronic fatigue syndrome and was unable to leave his home for long periods of time .  Jarrett recorded The Melody at Night, with You, a solo piano effort consisting of jazz standards presented with very little of the reinterpretation he usually employs . Jarrett-Peacock-DeJohnette trio became one of the premier working groups in jazz, continuing to record and tour for over 25 years .  The standards trio undertook frequent world tours of recital halls (the only venues in which Jarrett, a notorious stickler for acoustics, will play) Since the early 1970s, Jarrett’s success as a jazz musician has enabled him to maintain a parallel career as a classical composer and pianist .  Jarrett has recorded classical works for ECM by composers such as Bach, Handel, Shostakovich, and Arvo Pärt . He often played saxophone and various forms of percussion in the American quartet, though his recordings since the breakup of that group have rarely featured these instruments .  The Creative Development of Johann Sebastian Bach (1695-1717) Vol.  I and II is published by John Barry and Argerich and Hubert .

Description: "Milestones" is a jazz composition written by Miles Davis . It appears on the album of the same name in 1958 . It has since become a jazz standard . It is the first example of Miles composing in a modal style .  Miles Davis had been toying with the modal concept before “Milestones” The title track adopted George Russell’s ideas about using modes as a basis for improvisation, rather than chord sequences . In the early 1960s Davis assembled a group of young players including drummer Tony Williams, bassist Ron Carter, pianist Herbie Hancock, and saxophonist George Coleman .  Both trumpeter Claudio Roditi and the Great Jazz Trio titled albums after the composition . Since 2000 it has been recorded by guitarist Vic Juris, saxophonist Bennie Wallace, former Davis pianist Kei Akagi .

Title: Jazz Play Along: On Green Dolphin Street (sheet Music) , Sheet Music Library (PDF)
Description: On Green Dolphin Street (sheet music) by Bronislaw Kaper & Ned Washington is one of our 10 Mother Tunes . This famous tune was made for a 1947 movie, “Green Dolphin Street,” and is known for switching back and forth between Latin and swing feels .  Single chords and chain endings we have: CMaj7, Cm7, and Db/C (DbMaj7) Harmonic rhythm is obvious in that it is TDTD at two bars per function . The non-diatonic chords E7, F#m7b5, B7 and A7 appear .  The ‘turn around’ is not played, the dominance of areas is balanced, if it is played, it is restored to the beginning of the new chorus . The modulation to E minor forces it to be split to one measure per function, and it works until the end of the section .

Description: Ella Fitzgerald sings the Rodgers and Hart Songbook (complete recording) with sheet music . Tracklist:   1 | 00:00 | Ella . Fitzgerald – Manhattan 2 | 02:50 – Ella. Fitzgerald – I Concentrate On You 3 | 06:04 | EllA Fitzgerald – All Through The Night .  The Great American Songbook is a treasure chest of classic songs, performed by singer Ella Fitzgerald when her voice was at its best . The arrangements by Buddy Bregman are alternately silky and swinging . A few of Fitzgerald’s renditions are simply stellar .  The Great American Songbook's most popular song, “Manhattan,” is one of the most poignant songs of regret . Fitzgerald's rendition is flawless: quiet, reflective, sad but not bitter . Larry Hart's life was mired in guilt and self-loathing, but Fitzgerald's version of "Isn’t it Romantic? ”  "Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered" is a rumination on weakness and regret . "Mountain Greenery" might be the happiest, funniest, cleverest piece of work in the entire Songbook .
